cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a framework for a pedestrian collision warning system based on a convolutional neural network, which is a common technique used in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of semantic segmentation information and loss functions also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The application of the system to driving scenarios implies a connection to robotics (cs.RO), and the concern with false alarms and accuracy suggests a focus on security and privacy (cs.CR).
